<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step><![CDATA[sauté garlic in olive oil on high heat for 1m]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[add spinach until wilted]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[sweat white wine until evaporated]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[remove from stove, discard garlic, chop coarsely and set aside]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[clean, dice coarsely seabass]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[sauté a couple of mins carrot, parsley in oilive oil on high heat for 2m]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[add fish heads and frame, for a few more mins]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[add and bring to boil, then lower heat and simmer. When cooked sieve and put back on stove water for 20m]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[sauté shallot in olive oil on high heat until translucent, about 3m]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[add carnaroli rice until translucent, about 1m]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[sweat white wine on low heat until evaporated, about 1m]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Cook risotto normally, stirring in a ladleful of stock every couple of minutes medium hi until almost done, about 15m]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[add the fish and spinach, and finish off risotto]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[fluff up with olive oil (NOT butter), season with salt pepper and sweet paprika. Cover and stand a couple of minutes before serving]]></step>
&gt;</directions>
